<TITLE> Police arrest 1 for SI murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 24 (bdnews24.com)  Police have arrested one person allegedly in connection with the murder of Goutam Roy, sub-inspector of Bangshal Police Station. Toufik Mahbub Chowdhury, deputy commissioner of Dhaka Metropolitan Police, told bdnews24.com that Ahmed Ali Haider, 27, was at the spot and his companion had fired at the policeman. Goutam Roy was killed in Dholaikhal on April 20. Police arrested Haider from Bhajahari Street of Sutrapur on Friday night. The police has claimed that he is a mugger and extortionist. The deputy commissioner told bdnews24.com that Goutam had attempted to search Haider first on that fateful night when his mate Zakir fired his weapon. He also said that the search was on for Zakir. Newspapers reported that the sub-inspector was killed as part of plan by one fugitive, also among the top criminals of Dhaka, Dakat (dacoit) Shaheed. In reply to a question if Haider was a member of Dakat Shaheed's outfit, the commissioner said that he was not, but had information that Zakir was being pursued to join. Goutam was killed as he was searching three youths on Dholaikhal on his way home. bdnew
